    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-22T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-22T20:00:00-05:00" n="408"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.34522/55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-22T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 22, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>880. Reference Department’s telegram No. 772, October 21 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >20</hi>], 9 p.m. When the Salinas agreement was negotiated Congress was not
                    in session.</p>
                <p>When the Galápagos draft agreement was submitted Presidential powers had lapsed
                    consequently it was referred to Foreign Relations Committee whose chairman told
                    me today that changes mostly improvements in Spanish will be reported soon.</p>
                <p>I have been assured that if negotiations are not resumed before the adjournment
                    of Congress probably on October 29<note n="33" xml:id="d408fn33">The
                        negotiations were suspended until October 1943.</note> they will be handled
                    under special powers thereafter.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Panama for the information of General Andrews.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
